                            <comment id="17273150" author="emilles" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2021 21:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9648&quot; title=&quot;Bad error message when attempting to call a missing constructor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-9648&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-9648&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; made changes to&#160;&lt;tt&gt;groovy.lang.MetaClassImpl#invokeConstructor&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17273166" author="emilles" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2021 21:55:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Prior to the change in 3.0.6, the map coercion would create a non-static inner class instance, but it would not have a proper outer class reference.  Making the inner class static is compatible before and after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9648&quot; title=&quot;Bad error message when attempting to call a missing constructor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-9648&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-9648&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
